properties.name: delay
properties.description:
If there is only a single profile returned, this component automatically
redirects to the Microsoft Azure login. If a non-zero delay is specified
It waits delay seconds before redirecting.  This is intended to allow a
splash screen to display

properties.name: profilelist
properties.description:
If there are multiple profiles defined on the TRIRIGA server, and no profile
name is specified, the component doesn't automatically display the Microsoft
login page.  Instead it reports the list of profiles to the containing component
which must select a profile and initiate the login process.

properties.name: profilename
properties.description:
This is the name of a TRIRIG triOffice365 Config record to use for login.
The config record as the application key secret, and redirect URL.  The app
key effectively selects the office 365 instance, application rights, and the
list of valid redirect URL.  The redirect URL can be used to deal with proxy
servers or to select which TRIRIGA app to launch.

This can only be set for the

properties.name: scopes
properties.description:
Requested user scopes (rights).  Scopes in this list must be approved by the
user on first login.  These are different from those defined in the Microsoft
application definition which must be approved by the Office 365 instance
administrator

elements.description:
A Component that provides access to the Microsoft Outlook Event object which includes
Meetings, Appointments, and Reminders.

This version uses the Microsoft Graph API which provides access to cloud hosted versions
of Exchange, and to on-prem Exchange instances configured as hybrid installs.  That is
integrated with Azure active directory.

properties.name: authtoken
properties.description: Microsoft OAuth access token. typical returned from azure-oauth2

properties.name: eventlist
properties.description:
List of Microsoft Outlook events - meeting, appointments, reminders
for the current user populated by getList().
This list is paged

properties.name: fetchsize
properties.description: Maximum number of user entries to return in a query

properties.name: hasnextpage
properties.description: True if the User List has been successfully fetched and there are additional records to fetch

properties.name: outlookTimeZones
properties.description: List of Microsoft Outlook time zone support on the Exchange server and available to the current user

properties.name: timezone
properties.description:
Use this to specify the time zone for start and end times in the response.
If not specified, those time values are returned in UTC. Optional.
{
		name   : "microsoft timezone name",
     abbr   : "Standard abbriviation",
     offset : "offset from UTC"
}

methods.name: getEventList
methods.description:
Event List

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/calendar-list-events?view=graph-rest-1.0&tabs=cs

Retrieves all calendar events for the current user that meet the search criteria

methods.name: getEventListWithQuery
methods.description:
Event List

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/calendar-list-events?view=graph-rest-1.0&tabs=cs

Retrieves all calendar events for the current user that meet the query criteria

methods.name: getNextPage
methods.description:
Get the next page of people data using the same search as was used for getList

getList must have been called first, and a new call to getList resets the paging

elements.description:
A Component that provides access to the Microsoft Outlook User object. and provides
Current user context.

On startup, it makes a single query to get the logged TRIRIGA user and Outlook 365 user.
The TRIRIGA user is used to establish the Outlook 365 time zone for other Outlook 365 API
calls which require a time zone.

Access to the user object include:
 - Query a list of users
 - Create a user
 - Get details for an individual user
 - Update a User
 - Delete a User

This version uses the Microsoft Graph API which provides access to cloud hosted versions
of Exchange, and to on-prem Exchange instances configured as hybrid installs, that is
integrated with Azure active directory.

properties.description: Microsoft OAuth access token. typical returned from azure-oauth2

properties.name: fetchsize
properties.description: Maximum number of user entries to return in a query

properties.name: hasnextpage

properties.name: timezone

Use this to specify the time zone for start and end times in the response.
If not specified, those time values are returned in UTC. Optional.

List out Office/Outlook users populated by getList
This list is paged
